{"uri":"oai:oa.upm.es:34853","url":"file:///Users/cbadenes/Temp/ressist-resources/corpus/oaipmh/0158b2cf-8ba9-47f0-84f8-20899de0e592.pdf","source":{"name":"oa.upm.es","uri":"http://www.epnoi.org/oaipmh/oa.upm.es/cgi/oai2","url":"http://oa.upm.es/cgi/oai2","protocol":"oaipmh"},"metainformation":{"title":"PV Power Forecast Using a Nonparametric PV Model","published":"2015-04-06T07:01:07Z","format":"pdf","language":"eng","rights":"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/es/","description":"Forecasting the AC power output of a PV plant accurately is important both for plant owners and electric system operators. Two main categories of PV modeling are available: the parametric and the nonparametric. In this paper, a methodology using a nonparametric PV model is proposed, using as inputs several forecasts of meteorological variables from a Numerical Weather Forecast model, and actual AC power measurements of PV plants. The methodology was built upon the R environment and uses Quantile Regression Forests as machine learning tool to forecast AC power with a confidence interval. Real data from five PV plants was used to validate the methodology, and results show that daily production is predicted with an absolute cvMBE lower than 1.3%.","creators":[{"uri":"http://resources.ressist.es/author/Pinho-Almeida-M.","name":"M.","surname":"Pinho-Almeida"},{"uri":"http://resources.ressist.es/author/Perpi%C3%B1an%20Lamigueiro-Oscar","name":"Oscar","surname":"Perpiñan Lamigueiro"},{"uri":"http://resources.ressist.es/author/Narvarte%20Fern%C3%A1ndez-Luis","name":"Luis","surname":"Narvarte Fernández"}]},"bagOfWords":["forecast","model","power","variabl","scenario","perform","method","error","index","result","plant","statist","predict","differ","train","quantil","measur","between","irradi","daili","observ","clear","select","system","output","section","solar","includ","score","energi","skill","forest","comput","hourli","predictor","sever","locat","which","propos","input","interv","pres